d100 9
a108 4
<li>Devices are named by driver, not by type. So for example, there are no eth* devices. It would be ne0
for an ne2000 ethernet card, and xl0 for a 3Com Etherlink XL and Fast Etherlink XL ethernet device, etc.
<li>OpenBSD developers have made serious efforts to keep the manual pages up-to-date and accurate.  Use the <a href= "http://www.openbsd.org/cgi-bin/man.cgi?query=man">man(1)</a> command to find information.
</ul>
d124 1
a124 1
